→ inject additional context
———
hook output treated as from user`"]:::orange
    hooks --> hook_block{{"2.1.0 hook\nblocked?"}}:::teal
    hook_block -- "yes" --> submit_blocked["2.0.1 Blocked\n——————\nmessage does not proceed\nuser checks hook config"]:::red
    submit_blocked --> wait
    hook_block -- "no" --> assemble

    assemble["`**3.0.0 Assemble Context**
———
system prompt
→ role · safety rules · tool instructions
→ output efficiency · risk guidelines
→ --system-prompt / --append-system-prompt
  overrides (if provided)
CLAUDE.md chain
→ project rules (root → each nested dir)
→ overrides default behavior
memory (loaded from files)
→ user: role, preferences, knowledge
→ feedback: corrections + confirmed approaches
→ project: ongoing work, decisions, deadlines
→ reference: external system pointers
system reminders (injected each turn)
→ deferred tool names
→ available skill list
→ current date
→ CLAUDE.md contents
conversation history
→ all prior turns in session
→ or rehydrated from resumed session
→ includes: user msgs, model responses,
  tool calls, tool results
git status snapshot (captured once at start)
tool schemas
→ built-in: full JSONSchema always present
→ deferred: names only until ToolSearch
→ MCP: full schemas from connected servers
multimodal content (if present)
→ images: rendered visually (PNG, JPG, etc.)
→ PDFs: parsed text (max 20 pages per read)
→ notebooks: all cells with outputs`"]:::orange

    assemble --> generate["`**4.0.0 Generate**
———
extended thinking (hidden from user)
→ analyze request against full context
→ recall relevant memory
  (user prefs, feedback, project state)
→ check tool results for prompt injection
  (flag suspicious content to user
  before continuing)
→ assess risk and reversibility
  (local + reversible = proceed,
  shared + destructive = confirm first)
→ plan approach (simplest first)
→ select tools
→ consider permission implications
———
produces single response
(streamed token-by-token to terminal):
→ text output (markdown, highlighted)
→ tool calls (0 or more)
———
parallel: independent calls in one batch
sequential: dependent calls across batches
———
state modifiers (if active):
→ plan mode: restricted to read-only tools
  (no Edit, Write, NotebookEdit)
→ worktree: isolated git environment`"]:::yellow

    generate -. "Escape (cancel)" .-> cancelled["4.0.2 Cancelled\n——————\ngeneration interrupted\npartial output preserved\nin conversation history"]:::red
    cancelled --> wait

    generate --> has_tools{{"4.1.0 tool calls\nin response?"}}:::teal
    has_tools -- "no" --> display["4.0.1 Display Text\n——————\nstreamed markdown rendered\ncode blocks syntax-highlighted\ntoken usage + cost tracked"]:::cyan
    display --> stop_hooks

    has_tools -- "yes" --> batch["5.0.0 For each tool call in batch"]:::purple
    batch --> deferred{{"5.1.0 deferred tool?\n(schema unknown)"}}:::teal
    deferred -- "yes" --> toolsearch["5.0.1 ToolSearch\n——————\nquery matches deferred list\nreturns full JSONSchema\ntool becomes callable"]:::cyan
    toolsearch --> perm
    deferred -- "no" --> perm

    perm{{"5.2.0 permission\ncheck"}}:::teal
    perm -- "auto-allow\n(allowlist match or\n--dangerously-skip-permissions)" --> pre_hooks
    perm -- "needs approval" --> approve{{"5.3.0 user\napproves?"}}:::yellow
    approve -- "yes" --> pre_hooks
    approve -- "no" --> denied["5.0.2 Denied\n——————\ndo not re-attempt same call\nadjust approach or ask user"]:::red
    denied --> generate

    pre_hooks{{"6.1.0 PreToolUse\nhook fires"}}:::teal
    pre_hooks -- "hook blocks" --> hook_deny["6.0.1 Hook Blocked\n——————\ntreated as user denial\nmodel adjusts approach"]:::red
    hook_deny --> generate
    pre_hooks -- "allows or\nno hooks" --> exec

    exec["`**7.0.0 Execute Tool**
———
⟳ filesystem
→ Read (file · image · PDF · notebook)
→ Edit (string replacement;
  fails if file not yet Read)
→ Write (create or overwrite;
  fails if existing file not yet Read)
→ Glob (pattern-match file paths)
→ Grep (ripgrep content search)
———
⟳ execution
→ Bash (shell command, sandboxed by default;
  dangerouslyDisableSandbox to override;
  foreground or background mode;
  configurable timeout, default 120s max 600s)
→ LSP (language server protocol query)
———
⟳ user interaction
→ AskUserQuestion (see 8.0.0)
→ Config (change theme · model · settings
  without model invocation)
———
⟳ agent orchestration
→ Agent (spawn subagent — see 8.1.0)
→ SendMessage (continue existing subagent,
  preserves its full context)
→ Skill (expand + execute skill prompt)
———
⟳ external
→ MCP tools (call MCP server endpoints)
→ WebFetch (HTTP request)
→ WebSearch (web search query)
→ ToolSearch (resolve deferred tool schema)
→ ReadMcpResource (read MCP resources)
———
⟳ state transitions
→ EnterPlanMode (restrict to read-only tools)
→ ExitPlanMode (restore full tool set)
→ EnterWorktree (isolated git copy)
→ ExitWorktree (return to main working dir)
→ NotebookEdit (modify notebook cells)
———
⟳ scheduled
→ CronCreate · CronList · CronDelete
→ RemoteTrigger (invoke remote agent)`"]:::orange

    exec -. "Escape (cancel)" .-> cancelled

    exec --> post_hooks["7.0.1 PostToolUse Hooks Fire\n——————\nhook sees tool name + result\ncan log · validate · alert"]:::cyan
    post_hooks --> result{{"7.1.0 result?"}}:::teal

    result -- "error" --> error["7.0.2 Error Captured\n——————\nerror in result payload\n(tool failure · timeout · sandbox\nviolation · precondition failure)\nmodel sees on next generation\nadjusts approach — no blind retry\ndiagnoses root cause first"]:::red
    error --> more

    result -- "success" --> dispatch{{"7.2.0 special\npost-execution?"}}:::teal

    dispatch -- "AskUserQuestion" --> ask_user["`**8.0.0 Ask User**
———
synchronous pause mid-turn:
→ question displayed to user
→ tool execution loop pauses
→ awaits user's typed answer
→ answer becomes the tool result
———
only tool that requires user input
during execution (permission checks
are before execution, this is during)
———
used when model needs clarification
before proceeding with ambiguous
or high-stakes decisions`"]:::yellow
    ask_user --> more

    dispatch -- "Agent spawn" --> agent["`**8.1.0 Spawn Subagent**
———
creates isolated child process:
→ fresh context window
→ inherits: CLAUDE.md chain, settings,
  permissions, working directory
→ does NOT inherit: parent conversation
  history, loaded memory, parent context
———
typed specialization:
→ Explore (fast codebase search,
  no Edit, Write, Agent)
→ Plan (architecture + research,
  no Edit, Write, NotebookEdit)
→ general-purpose (full tool set)
→ custom (user-defined agent types)
———
model override:
→ can specify sonnet, opus, or haiku
→ default: inherits parent's model
———
execution modes:
→ foreground: parent blocks until done
→ background: parent continues working,
  notified asynchronously on completion
  (multiple bg agents run concurrently,
  each with independent notification)
———
isolation modes:
→ shared: same working directory
→ worktree: temporary git branch + copy,
  changes stay on separate branch,
  worktree path returned if modified,
  auto-cleaned if no changes made
———
subagent lifecycle:
→ runs own 4.0.0 → 7.x.x loop recursively
  (full generate → route → execute → feedback)
→ can be continued via SendMessage
  (resumes with full context preserved)
→ on completion: single result to parent
→ subagent context then discarded`"]:::yellow
    agent --> collect["8.0.2 Collect Result\n——————\nresult message returned\nto parent context"]:::cyan
    collect --> more

    dispatch -- "standard tool" --> more{{"7.3.0 more calls\nin batch?"}}:::purple
    more -- "yes" --> batch
    more -- "no" --> feedback["7.0.3 Feed Results\n——————\nall batch results appended\nas tool-result turn in history\nsystem reminders re-injected\n(deferred tools · skills ·\nmemory · date · CLAUDE.md)"]:::cyan
    feedback --> turns{{"7.4.0 --max-turns\nreached?"}}:::teal
    turns -- "no" --> generate
